 :RTFM: /R·T·F·M/, imp. [Unix] Abbreviation for `Read The Fucking Manual'. 1.
Used by {guru}s to brush off questions they consider trivial or annoying.
Compare {Don't do that then!}. 2. Used when reporting a problem to indicate
that you aren't just asking out of {randomness}. "No, I can't figure out how
to interface Unix to my toaster, and yes, I have RTFM." Unlike sense 1, this
use is considered polite. see also {FM}, {RTFAQ}, {RTFB}, {RTFS}, {STFW},
{RTM}, all of which mutated from RTFM, and compare {UTSL}.